premise 2 is not necessarily sound. 

An example was given that a golfer who wants and focuses on swinging good swings horribly.

Again, I think that hedonism tells you what you intrinsically want can't be wrong. But wanting to swing good is instrumental. its a bad analogy to "wanting happiness gives you less happiness".

